{% comment %}
  Required:
  	nothing

  Notes: Used to render font links (normally Google Fonts)
  	   on all existing layout files. Currently the stylesheet
  	   is being preloaded, but this should be tested to make sure
  	   it does help with speed. Whether or not it does is dependent on the
  	   specific project. (Too much preloading, or preloading
  	   massive resources, will backfire)


<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link
  rel="preload"
  as="style"
  href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat:wght@400;800&display=swap"
  onload="this.onload=null; this.rel='stylesheet';"
  crossorigin
>

{% endcomment %}

{% comment %}
  Font-Face Examples

  Notes: Whenever possible, font files should be added to the assets folder
         in woff2 and woff format, and defined as font faces here. This allows
         the download of the fonts to be separate from the main stylesheet, and
         speeds up rendering. Local fonts are preferred for the sake of less
         third-party network requests.
{% endcomment %}

{% style %}
	@font-face {
  		font-family: "Courier Prime";
  		font-style: normal;
  		font-display:swap;
  		font-weight: 800;
  		src: url('{{ "courier-prime.woff2" | asset_url }}') format('woff2'),
			 url('{{ "courier-prime.woff" | asset_url }}') format('woff');
  	}
{% endstyle %}
